In this proclamation, President Donald J. Trump recognizes the American workers on Labor Day and emphasizes their role in the country's economic resurgence. The president highlights his administration's pro-growth policies that have resulted in the addition of 6 million new jobs and near record-low unemployment rates. He also discusses efforts to prepare the American workforce for the future, including the establishment of the President's National Council for the American Worker and the promotion of apprenticeships and expanded access to education and training programs. Additionally, President Trump mentions the renegotiation of trade agreements to obtain fairer terms for American companies and workers. The proclamation concludes with a call to honor and celebrate the contributions of working Americans.